title: clickToDetail1
desc: This is a basic example that demonstrates rendering components based on URLs with react-router as well as connecting them to Redux state. It uses both <Link> elements as well as the push action creator provided by react-router-redux.

title: clickToDetail2
desc: This example also demonstrates integration with redux-devtools ^3.0.0

title: clickToDetail3
desc: If you want to run the example from the npm published version of react-router-redux, remove the alias in webpack.config to the source from line 21.
